 Human romantic relationships are vital, and require a mutual build-up of romantic feelings. One of the more obvious, albeit primitive, methods of creating such a build-up is through attending a marriage proposal. The act of attending a marriage proposal, given a certain set of identifiable preferences, can often be observed as one of the most efficient means of increasing one's romantic feelings as a function of time. The increase in romantic feelings is also often considered to be one of the primitive functions of the act
